  "prompt": "What is a good way to say \u6a2a\u5411\u5377\u8f74rpg\u6e38\u620f in English?",
  "response": "There are several ways to translate \"\u6a2a\u5411\u5377\u8f74rpg\u6e38\u620f\" into English, depending on the nuance you want to convey. Here are a few options, ranked from most literal to more idiomatic:\n\n*   **Literal:**\n\n    *   **Side-scrolling RPG:** This is the most direct and common translation.  It accurately describes the genre.\n    *   **Horizontal scrolling RPG:** Slightly more precise than \"side-scrolling\" but less commonly used.\n\n*   **More Idiomatic/Descriptive:**\n\n    *   **Side-scroller RPG:** A more concise version of \"side-scrolling RPG\" that is also widely understood.\n    *   **2D Action RPG (with side-scrolling):** This specifies the visual style (2D) and emphasizes the action element often present in these games. You would use this if the game has a strong action component in addition to RPG elements.\n    *   **Platformer RPG:** If the game has a lot of platforming elements (jumping, climbing, etc.) in addition to RPG mechanics, this might be appropriate.  But be careful, as many platformers have light RPG elements without being true RPGs.\n    *   **2D RPG:**  While this doesn't explicitly mention side-scrolling, the \"2D\" aspect often implies a side-scrolling or top-down perspective, and in many contexts people will understand you mean a side-scrolling 2D RPG.\n\n**When choosing, consider these factors:**\n\n*   **Specificity:** Do you need to be extremely precise about the genre?\n*   **Target Audience:**  Are you talking to gamers familiar with genre terminology, or a more general audience?\n*   **Emphasis:** Which aspect of the game do you want to highlight (the side-scrolling, the RPG elements, the action, the platforming)?\n\n**Recommendation:**\n\nIn most cases, **\"Side-scrolling RPG\"** or **\"Side-scroller RPG\"** are the best and most widely understood translations. They're clear, concise, and accurately describe the genre. If you want to highlight action elements, consider \"2D Action RPG (with side-scrolling).\"\n",
